I"a
<h4 id="example">Example</h4>
<p>\(\int_{x} N\left(x ; \mu_{1}, \sigma_{1}^{2}\right) N\left(x ; y,
\sigma_{2}^{2}\right) d x=N\left(y ; \mu_{1},
\sigma_{1}^{2}+\sigma_{2}^{2}\right)\)</p>

<p>The key to prove this equation above is \(\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-x^{2}} d x=\sqrt{\pi}\).</p>

